===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable}} The act of [[uniting]] or [[join]]ing two or more things into one.
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The state of being united or [[join]]ed.
# {{lb|en|countable}} That which is united, or made one; something formed by a combination or [[coalition]] of parts or members; a [[confederation]]; a [[consolidate]]d body; a [[league]].
# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[trade union]]; a workers' union.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1918|author={{w|W. B. Maxwell}}|chapter=22
|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL1097634W The Mirror and the Lamp]
|passage=In the autumn there was a row at some cement works about the unskilled labour men. A '''union''' had just been started for them and all but a few joined. One of these blacklegs was laid for by a picket and knocked out of time.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} An association of students at a university for social and/or political purposes; also in some cases a debating body.
# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[joint]] or other connection uniting parts of [[machinery]], such as [[pipe]]s.
# {{lb|en|countable|set theory}} The [[set]] containing all of the [[element]]s of two or more sets.
# {{lb|en|countable}} The act or state of [[marriage]].
# {{lb|en|uncountable|archaic|euphemistic}} [[sexual intercourse|Sexual intercourse]].
# {{lb|en|countable|programming}} A [[data structure]] that can store any of various types of item, but only one at a time.
# {{lb|en|countable|now|_|rare|archaic}} A large, high-quality [[pearl]].
#* {{RQ:Burton Melancholy|part=II|section=3|member=3|passage=Nonius the senator hath a purple coat as stiff with jewels as his mind is full of vices; rings on his fingers worth 20,000 sesterces, and{{...}}an '''union''' in his ear worth an hundred pounds' weight of gold {{...}} }}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|passage=And in the cup an union shall he throw, Richer than that which four successive kings In Denmark's crown have worn.}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} An [[affiliation]] of several [[parish]]es for [[joint]] [[support]] and [[management]] of their [[poor]]; also the jointly-owned [[workhouse]].

